        "start_line": 537,
        "end_line": 559,
        "caption": "Main results regarding the radio emission from the modelled stellar BSs. Column 3 shows the power injected in the RS by the stellar wind typically, $L_{\\rm w\\perp} \\approx 0.5 - 0.7 L_{\\rm w}$). Columns 4--6 are model parameters: the fraction of the injected power that goes into electrons, the electrons-to-magnetic energy density ratio, and the IL width parameter; we fix $\\eta_{\\rm B} = 0.2$ for all systems. Column 7 summarises our conclusions about the origin of the emission of each source.",
